        <h1>SAFETY GUIDELINES</h1>
        <p class="subtitle">DRDL - Safety Fire Request Procedures</p>

        <h2>1. PERSONAL PROTECTIVE EQUIPMENT (PPE)</h2>
        <ul>
            <li>All personnel must wear appropriate PPE based on the hazard level assigned to their task.</li>
            <li>Inspect all PPE before use for any signs of damage, wear, or defects.</li>
            <li>Replace damaged or worn-out PPE immediately to ensure continued protection.</li>
            <li>Ensure proper fit and secure fastenings of all protective equipment.</li>
            <li>Keep PPE clean and maintained according to manufacturer specifications.</li>
        </ul>

        <h2>2. WORK SITE SAFETY</h2>
        <ul>
            <li>Conduct a thorough safety assessment before commencing any work activities.</li>
            <li>Mark and cordon off all hazardous areas with warning signs.</li>
            <li>Maintain clear communication with all team members throughout the work period.</li>
            <li>Keep emergency exits and safety equipment easily accessible at all times.</li>
            <li>Ensure adequate lighting and ventilation in all work areas.</li>
            <li>Post emergency contact numbers prominently at the work site.</li>
        </ul>

        <h2>3. HAZARDOUS ACTIVITIES</h2>
        <ul>
            <li>Only trained and authorized personnel are permitted to handle hazardous materials.</li>
            <li>Follow all prescribed procedures for each hazardous activity without exception.</li>
            <li>Do not deviate from approved work plans under any circumstances.</li>
            <li>Maintain proper ventilation and environmental controls during hazardous operations.</li>
            <li>Implement containment measures to prevent environmental contamination.</li>
            <li>Regularly review and update standard operating procedures (SOPs).</li>
        </ul>

        <h2>4. EMERGENCY PROCEDURES</h2>
        <ul>
            <li>All personnel must know the location of emergency equipment including first aid kits and fire extinguishers.</li>
            <li>Report all incidents, near-misses, and injuries immediately to the site supervisor.</li>
            <li>Have emergency contact numbers readily available and accessible.</li>
            <li>Conduct emergency drills regularly to ensure preparedness.</li>
            <li>Evacuate immediately when instructed by the safety officer.</li>
            <li>Seek medical attention for any injuries, no matter how minor they appear.</li>
        </ul>

        <h2>5. DOCUMENTATION AND COMPLIANCE</h2>
        <ul>
            <li>Maintain accurate records of all safety activities and incidents.</li>
            <li>Complete all required safety documentation before work commencement.</li>
            <li>Ensure compliance with organizational safety policies and regulations.</li>
            <li>Notify the Safety Division telephonically before commencing activity.</li>
            <li>Provide adequate time and resources for safety training.</li>
            <li>Maintain updated emergency contact information and procedures.</li>
        </ul>

        <h2>6. SUPERVISOR RESPONSIBILITIES</h2>
        <ul>
            <li>Ensure all team members receive proper training on safety protocols.</li>
            <li>Conduct regular safety briefings before commencing work.</li>
            <li>Monitor and enforce compliance with all safety guidelines.</li>
            <li>Investigate and report all safety incidents promptly.</li>
            <li>Provide feedback and recognize safe work practices.</li>
            <li>Review and improve safety procedures based on lessons learned.</li>
        </ul>

        <h2>7. ACCOUNTABILITY</h2>
        <ul>
            <li>All personnel are responsible for maintaining a safe work environment.</li>
            <li>Any violation of safety guidelines may result in disciplinary action.</li>
            <li>Supervisors will be held accountable for ensuring compliance of their teams.</li>
            <li>Work must not commence without proper safety clearance.</li>
        </ul>

